entity.Name: Account

Description.description: Business that represents a customer or potential customer. The company that is billed in business transactions.
The date on which the company’s relationship with the bank needs to be reviewed (i.e. account planning to be done).
Total amount remaining from the credit line/limit implemented against the client.
Value of the Available Limit in base currency.
Total revenue generated by the bank from the sales to the client and services utilized by the client in the current year.
Value of the Bank’s YTD Revenue in base currency.

displayname.description: Company’s Profit in the Last Year

Description.description: Total profit earned by the company in the previous year as reported by them in their financial reports.

displayname.description: Company’s Profit in the Last Year (Base)

Description.description: Value of the Company’s Profit in the Last Year in base currency.

displayname.description: Company Turnover in the last Year

Description.description: Company’s annual turnover amount as reported by them in their financial reports.

displayname.description: Company Turnover in the last Year (Base)

Description.description: Value of the Company Turnover in the last Year in base currency.
Number of days for which the client has been in Past Due status,
The bank’s branch at which customer was enrolled.
Total credit line/limit implemented in the core banking system or Limit Management System for the client to utilize.
Value of the Implemented Limit in base currency.
Date on which the company’s main credit line/limit will be expired.
The date on which the company missed the first payment against the borrowings.
Internal ranking of the commercial customer based on profitability to the bank
The rate of risk adjusted return on capital of the company.
The rating assigned to the client by the bank in overall risk as reported by risk rating tools such as Moody’s.
Company’s total deposits with our bank including all the savings, current, and deposit accounts.
Value of the Total Deposits in base currency.
Total credit line/limit assigned to the company by our bank.
Value of the Total Limit in base currency.
Company’s total loans with the bank,
Value of the Total Loans in base currency.
Total amount of borrowings for which the repayment by the client is overdue.
Value of the Total Past Due in base currency.
Total credit that has been utilized by the company from the assigned limit (by cash based and non-cash based borrowings).
Value of the Utilized Limit in base currency.
